<subsection xml:id="subsec-compound-interest">
    <title>Compound interest</title>
    <introduction>
        
        <p>
            In the previous sections, you learnt how to calculate simple interest.
        </p>
        <p>
            In this section, you will learn how to calculate another type of interest called <m>\textbf{compound interest.}</m>
        </p>
        
        
            
    </introduction>
    

    <subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-compound-interest">
        <title>Calculating compound interest step by step per annum in real life situation</title>
        <activity>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{work in groups}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                Consider a trader who deposited <m>Ksh. \, 50 \,000</m> in a bank in a certain year.
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(i).">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            If interest of <m>5\%</m> was earned that year, calculate the interest.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the total amount of money in the account the end of that year.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            In the second year, the trader earned <m>5\%</m> interest on the total 
                            amount i the first year.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            In the third year, the trader earned <m>5\%</m> interest on the total amount in the second 
                            year.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the total amount of money in the account at the end 
                            of the third year.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Subtract the initial deposit from the total amount of money 
                            in the account at the end of the third year.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Discuss and compare result with other groups.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Key Takeaway:}}</m>
        </p>

        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Compound interest}</m> is the interest where the principal keeps changing each year.
        </p>
        <p>
            The principal of any year is the sum of the principal and the interest of the previous year.
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Compound interest}</m> is the total interest earned in all the year.
        </p>




        <p>
            The difference between the amount derived from accumulated interest 
            and the initial amount is the compound interest.
        </p>

        <p>
            <m>\textbf{N/B:}</m>
            <m>\textbf{Simple Interest}</m> is calculated only on the 
            original principal,
           while <m>\textbf{Compound Interest}</m> is calculated on the 
           principal plus accumulated interest, making it
            grow over time that the principal was deposited.


        </p>

        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A trader took a loan of <m>Ksh. \, 400\,000</m> at the rate of <m>12\%</m> 
                    compound interest for three year. Find the total amount of interest repaid after three years.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{Interest at the end of the first year}=\amp \frac{P_1 RT}{100} </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 400\,000 \times \frac{12}{100} \times 1 </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp Ksh\, 48\,000 </mrow>
                        
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                   <md>
                    <mrow> \textbf{Principle}(P_2)=\amp \textbf{Initial principal}(p_1)+ \textbf{interest} </mrow>
                    <mrow>= \amp Ksh. \, 400\,000 + Ksh\, 48 \, 000 </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp Ksh. \, 448\,000 </mrow>
                   </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\text{Interest at the end of the second year}=\amp \frac{P_2 RT}{100} </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp Ksh. \, 448\,000 \times \frac{12}{100}  \times 1</mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp Ksh.\, 53\,760</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \textbf{Principle}(P_3)=\amp \textbf{Initial principal}(p_2)+ \textbf{interest} </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp Ksh. \, 448\,000 + Ksh. \, 53\,760  </mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp Ksh. \, 501\,760</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                   <md>
                     <mrow>\text{Interest at the end of the second year}(p_3)=\amp \frac{P_3 RT}{100} </mrow>
                     <mrow> =\amp Ksh. 501\,760 \times \frac{12}{100} \times 1 </mrow>
                     <mrow> =\amp Ksh. 60\,211.20 </mrow>
                   </md> 
                </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore, 
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \textbf{Compound interest}= \amp Ksh.(48\,000+53\, 760+60\,211.20)</mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp {\color{blue} Ksh. 161\,971.20 } </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Akinyi deposited <m>sh \,60 \,000</m> in a bank. The bank paid interest at the rate of <m>10\%</m> per annum. He withdrew all the 
                    money at the end of three years.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Calculate the compound interest after the three years.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                How much money was in his account by the end of the three years?
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="(a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <m>\text{Simple interest} = \text{principal} \times \text{rate} \times \text{time}</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> \text{First year's interest} =\amp sh\, 60\,000 \times \frac{10}{100} \times 1 </mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp sh\, 6\,000</mrow>
                                    
                                </md>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> \text{Second year's interest} =\amp (sh\, 60\,000  + sh\, 6\,000 )\times \frac{10}{100} \times 1 </mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \amp sh\, 66\,000 \times \frac{10}{100} \times 1</mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \amp sh\,6\,600 </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> \text{Third year's interest} =\amp (sh\, 66\,000  + sh\, 6\,600 )\times \frac{10}{100} \times 1 </mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \amp sh\,72\,600 \times \frac{10}{100} \times 1 </mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \amp sh\, 7\,260 </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>\text{Compound interest}=  \amp \text{total interest earned in the three years.} </mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp sh\,6\,000+sh\,6\,600+sh\,7\,260 </mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp {\color{blue} sh\, 19\,860 }</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> \textbf{Amount after three years}=\amp \textbf{initial principal} + \textbf{total interest} </mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \amp sh\,60\,0000+sh\, 19\,860 </mrow>
                                    <mrow>= \amp {\color{blue} sh\,79\,860} </mrow>
                                </md> 
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        
    </subsubsection>





 



    
</subsection>